The paper discusses the need for greater scientific study of AI systems, particularly in areas such as fairness and algorithmic bias. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the barriers preventing social and behavioral scientists from conducting studies of AI systems, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.CY (computers and society) and cs.HC (human-computer interaction) sub-categories. The proposal of a two-sided marketplace for studying AI behavior suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.SI (social and information networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on methodology and the scientific study of AI systems suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.LG (machine learning) sub-category.
